CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1959, page A2, reads: "Coleman Second in YMCA Race - William H. Coleman, right center, pilot of the Spaceship Thor, receives congratulations from the Rev. S. Amos Brackeen, left center, Chief of Staff, in membership enrollment drive which ended Monday night. The Thor finished second.  Some of the crew members look on, with smiles.  They are, left to right: Frank Lane, Luther Sewell, Frank Bolden, Leroy Lowry, the Rev. Mr. Brackeen, Patrolman Sam Wilson, Mr. Coleman, Beverly Hunt Sr., William Green, J.D. Lewis Sr., Robert Smiley and Russell Washington. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Luther Sewell, Patrolman Sam Wilson, Frank Lane, William H. Coleman, and Robert Smiley, posed in front of membership toteboard inscribed "The Thor Spaceship"
